The 2019 edition of the Information Communication Technology and Telecommunication Exhibition (ICTEL EXPO) begins today in Lagos. The summit, according to the organisers, will give a 360˚ view of the West African ICT and telecoms industry, giving top visibility to sweeping trends, innovation as well as providing an excellent networking opportunity for business decision makers. ICTEL EXPO, which started in 2015 by the Lagos Chamber of Commerce and Industry (LCCI) is a professional trade show that focuses on the Information Communication Technology (ICT) and Telecommunications industry. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE A statement by LCCI head of corporate communications, Segun Alabi said the EXPO will provide veritable platforms for comprehensive overview of trends, new ideas as well as allow suppliers and providers meet face to face and network with other professional in the ICT & Telecommunication sector. According to the statement, Mr. Uwem Uwem Akpan, Entrepreneurship Programme Manager at Tony Elumelu Foundation and Professor Yinka David-West, Academic Director and Professor of Information Systems at Lagos Business School are expected to deliver keynote addresses at the two-day event themed ‘Fourth Industrial Revolution: The Nigerian Story’.  Shittu, others to brainstorm at ICTEL Expo 2017 ICT needs enabling environment to thrive - LCCI president FG approves ICT roadmap Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin